<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-08T17:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-08T17:30:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Detention/2: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ciudad Juarez</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dye</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">El
                                        Paso, Tex</hi></placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-08T15:30:00-07:00">March 8, 1929—3:30
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:54 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Agreed between commanders that General Ramos and his Federal troops cross
                            into United States and be interned. This to proceed at once. Fort Bliss
                            military police in charge of the plan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dye</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>